&gt;
&gt; Ooops, not so elegant.  Referring to my post
&gt; just a little earlier, --- there is no ref to
&gt; the Parent URI (&quot;curi&quot;) in the schedule method.
&gt; So will be hard to copy info from parent to
&gt; child URI.  This needs more thought.
&gt; D.

Try &#39;CandidateURI#getVia&#39;.  Returned type is Object but in an override 
context should always be an UURI instance.

I also did some more refactoring.  I made handleLinkCollection protected 
(handlePrerequisites already was protected rather than private) and 
added createCandidateUri, a method that both handleLinkCollection and 
handlePrerequisites use to create a CandidateURI instance.

Let us know if this is still not sufficent -- or if you have better 
refactoring suggestion.

Yours,
St.Ack

